    <h2>Signs Your Melbourne Chimney Needs Cleaning</h2>
    <p>If any of these are familiar, it is time to get it sorted before another Melbourne winter arrives:</p>
    <div class="reason-grid">
      <div class="rc"><span class="rc-icon">&#128293;</span><div class="rc-title">Smoke coming back in</div><div class="rc-desc">Most common sign of a blocked or heavily sooted flue. A clean usually fixes this immediately.</div></div>
      <div class="rc"><span class="rc-icon">&#128168;</span><div class="rc-title">Persistent smoky smell</div><div class="rc-desc">Creosote or old ash in the flue causes a burnt odour even when the fire hasn&rsquo;t been lit.</div></div>
      <div class="rc"><span class="rc-icon">&#9888;&#65039;</span><div class="rc-title">Weak or sluggish draw</div><div class="rc-desc">Fires that won&rsquo;t start easily or keep dying down &mdash; restricted airflow in the flue.</div></div>
      <div class="rc"><span class="rc-icon">&#127810;</span><div class="rc-title">Pre-winter service</div><div class="rc-desc">Book in March&ndash;May before the rush &mdash; wait times blow out in June once winter sets in.</div></div>
      <div class="rc"><span class="rc-icon">&#128203;</span><div class="rc-title">Overdue for annual clean</div><div class="rc-desc">Used regularly through winter? It needs cleaning once a year regardless of symptoms.</div></div>
